name: As a user, if I click Lines per page "25", the number of rows in the employee table should reflect the correct count.

steps.name: Given Navigate to Dashboard with "english" language
Then verify that dashboard page tab name contains QUGEM
When I click the Employee_Master_data module
When I select "GESAMT FIRMEN" using the company selection button, and choose "All" using the client selection button"
When I delete if in any row, surname column text is tester or developer
page.waitForSelector(//h2[contains(text(),'Are you sure you want to permanently delete?')])
locator.textContent(//h2[contains(text(),'Are you sure you want to permanently delete?')])
Then verify if you write tester or developer in filter surname, row1 is invisible
Then I delete all filter sections to start every test Scenario with a clear filter
When I check if Lines per page select button is functional and visible
Then I click "25" employee choose in Lines Per Page
Then I verify the number of rows in employee table is not more than the "25"
Then I verify next page button is visible and clickable
Then I click employee table next page button , and verify number of rows are not more than "25"
Then I click previous page button is visible and clickable
Then I click employee table previous page button , and verify number of rows are not more than "25"
